-- Steel Authority of India May Raise as Much as $3.5 Billion in Share Sale
-- Pratik Parija
-- 2010-09-20T05:54:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/steel-authority-of-india-may-raise-as-much-as-3-5-billion-in-share-sale.html

          
          
             Steel Authority of India Ltd. may
raise as much as 160 billion rupees in a planned share sale,
Steel Minister Virbhadra Singh told reporters in New Delhi.  
 The sale is scheduled to start before the financial year
ends on March 31, Singh said.  
 Steel Authority is “open” to give Posco a majority stake
in a venture, Singh said. The proposal must be approved by the
Cabinet, he said.  
